---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import SpeakerModal from '../../components/SpeakerModal.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Oxford LLMs 2024"
  description="Oxford LLMs 2024 — second annual workshop on AI for social science. Nuffield College, September 2024."
>

  <!-- ── Breadcrumb strip ───────────────────────────────────── -->
  <aside class="status-strip" aria-label="Page breadcrumb">
    <div class="status-strip-inner">
      <a href="/summer-school/" style="color:inherit; text-decoration:none;">Summer School</a>
      <span class="sep"></span>
      <span>2024 — Second edition</span>
    </div>
  </aside>

  <!-- ── Report hero ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="report-hero">
    <div class="rh-inner">
      <div>
        <p class="rh-kicker">Second edition · September 2024</p>
        <span class="rh-year">2024</span>
        <p class="rh-title">Nuffield College, Oxford — five-day intensive on AI for social science.</p>
        <div class="rh-stats">
          <div class="rh-stat"><span class="rh-n">30</span><span class="rh-l">Participants</span></div>
          <div class="rh-stat"><span class="rh-n">~200</span><span class="rh-l">Applications</span></div>
          <div class="rh-stat"><span class="rh-n">5</span><span class="rh-l">Days</span></div>
          <div class="rh-stat"><span class="rh-n">16</span><span class="rh-l">Speakers</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rh-photo">
        <img src="/img/posts/report_2024/group_llms_2024.jpg" alt="Oxford LLMs 2024 cohort at Nuffield College" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── § 01 About ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section-v3 section-v3--marker" id="about">
    <span class="section-number">§ 01 · About</span>
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head-v3 reveal">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow-v3" style="margin-bottom:14px">Second edition</div>
          <h2 class="h-section">RAG, fine-tuning, and a live research project.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lede-v3">
          Nuffield College, supported by the Oxford Van Houten Fund, ran an intensive five-day workshop
          on AI for social science in late September 2024.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal" style="max-width: 72ch;">
        <p class="copy" style="margin: 0 0 18px;">
          We received just under 200 applications and selected 30 participants. The lecture series
          developed by Grigory Sapunov, Tatiana Shavrina, and Ilya Boytsov covered LLM foundations,
          transformer architecture, in-context learning, emergent reasoning, agent-based systems,
          fine-tuning methods, and self-hosting. Applied tutorials demonstrated retrieval-augmented
          generation and observability tools for model monitoring.
        </p>
        <p class="copy" style="margin: 0 0 18px;">
          Established scholars including Lisa P. Argyle, Chris Barrie, Raymond Duch, Thomas Hegghammer,
          Neil Ketchley, Alison Koh, and Alexis Palmer shared current research using LLMs.
          Guest practitioners from Qdrant, Ori Cloud, Arize, and Google led practical seminars on
          vector search, GPU infrastructure, observability, and AI deployment.
        </p>
        <p class="copy" style="margin: 0;">
          All participants contributed to the main research project: developing an approach for
          survey data preprocessing aimed at training LLMs to predict people's opinions and
          self-reported behaviours.
          <a href="https://www.ori.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ori Cloud</a> provided GPU
          support. Models and datasets are published on the
          <a href="https://huggingface.co/oxford-llms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Oxford LLMs Hugging Face profile</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

